items.name: 12-Gauge CHAC Shell
items.description: 12-Gauge CHAC Shell is an advanced purchaseable buckshot ammunition that does up to 450 damage. It pairs well with the CHAC "Boomstick" Shotgun that can also be purchased from the Workshop .

items.name: 7.62mm CHAC Round
items.description: 7.62mm CHAC Round is a purchaseable type of Rifle Ammunition for use in any Rifle .

items.name: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine I
items.description: Anti-Parasitic Vaccine I is purchased in the Workshop on the Space Station . Vaccines are long lasting preventatives of aliments on Icarus, they provide a unqiue Status Effect , which makes surviving the enviroment without worry possible.

items.name: Anti-Poison Paste
items.description: Anti-Poison Paste is one of the multiple, easily overlooked recipes available in the tier 1 tech tree. Reduces the duration of Poison from critters like the Venomous Fish or the Caveworm .

items.name: CHAC "Boomstick" Shotgun
items.description: The CHAC "Boomstick" Shotgun is an advanced purchaseable Shotgun with increase projectile and critical damage. It fires any Shotgun Ammunition and is comparable to other Tier 4  Firearms .

items.name: CHAC "Sovereign" Rifle
items.description: The CHAC "Sovereign" Rifle is a purchaseable rifle with a fast reload speed and moderate damage capability.

items.name: Crafting
items.description: Crafting is the skill that enables many of the other ways prospectors pursue their goals on Icarus. While they can gather Food with their bare hands, and can attempt to Hunt with their fists, everything they attempt on the moon's surface is facilitated by crafting.

items.name: KickFall Module
items.description: This module increases resistance to fall damage by 40% when equipped in an Envirosuit module slot, reducing the amount of damage received when falling. It can be researched and crafted on the Space Station in the Workshop . Multiple Kick Fall Modules may be equipped if the Prospector has available slots on their Envirosuit. The resistance increase from each Kick Fall Module will stack and will grant near immunity to fall damage if four are equipped. Falling resistance now caps at 99%.

items.name: Kiwifruit
items.description: Kiwifruit are a fresh fruit that can be eaten raw for a small boost in stamina and resistance to cave sickness or used in additional Food recipes.

items.name: MXC Fuel Canister
items.description: The MXC Fuel Canister is purchased from the Workshop on the Space Station and is used for Biofuel storage. It comes prefilled with fuel when purchased and can be refilled at the Biofuel Composter , Electric Composter or by interacting with a Portable Biofuel Tank deployed on the ground. It can be taken back to Orbit and will remain filled, allowing the Prospector to use it across multiple prospects. It does not fill when returned to station. It holds 10 liters of Biofuel.

items.name: MXC Hydrazine Canister
items.description: The MXC Hydrazine Canister is purchased from the Workshop on the Space Station and stores 10,000 litres of hydrazine. The fuel is used in several other MXC devices by placing the canister in the device's inventory slot. The fuel canister cannot be refilled.

items.name: MXC Venom Arrow
items.description: The MXC Venom Arrow is ammunition used with a Bow . Like bolts and javelins, they may be recovered after being fired into the ground or an animal carcass.

items.name: MXC Venom Arrow Bundle
items.description: Consuming the bundle will add 5x MXC Venom Arrow to the Prospectors inventory, must be consumed after dropping into a prospect. Consumed arrow bundles cannot be taken back to the space station. Arrow bundles that have not been consumed can be taken back to the space station for use in another prospect.

items.name: Shengong 'Liwei' O2 Tank
items.description: It is worth noting that this Oxygen Container takes 65 Oxite to fill at a Oxite Dissolver , and will last significantly longer than an Oxygen Bladder , making it one of the most valuable early game purchases in the Workshop . Will remain filled between Prospects. It holds 6500 oxygen units making it useful for stockpile missions that require oxygen delivery.

items.name: Stone Pickaxe
items.description: The Stone Pickaxe is the first Pickaxe available to prospectors and is used to break apart mineable Minerals , reducing them to usable resources. Stone, Sulfur, Oxite, Silica, Coal, Salt, Copper, Iron, Gold, and Exotic nodes can be mined with a Stone Pickaxe. To mine Aluminium, Platinum, and Titanium, prospectors must use a Steel Pickaxe or better.

items.name: Talents
items.description: With 465 combined talents to choose from, Icarus' talent trees give prospectors the ability to construct their own unique play-styles inside of five primary Categories: Survival, Adventure, Habitation, Combat and Solo Talents Trees.

items.name: UDA Aluminium Ore Resource Supply
items.description: Despite the usefulness of these supply packs, they are quite expensive when used often (ideal for creative builds). Don't feel like running out to gather materials, and you're out of Ren? Exotics can be sold for Ren under the Workshop tab while at the station, and Ren can be obtained by completing SMPL3 missions using the Short Range Radio .
